      "title": "ℹ️ About — BrainDead GLSL Skin Tinting",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# 🧠 BrainDead — GLSL Skin Tinting\n\nGPU-accelerated GLSL batch shader — generate **4 skin tone variations** (light / medium / dark / zombie) from a single source image in **one pass**. No re-sampling per iteration; all tones render sequentially on GPU via `BD_GLSLBatch`, then `BD_SaveBatch` writes one labeled PNG per tone.\n\n## Flow\n1. **Load Image** — load a character render (RGBA art recommended; alpha = art over tint).\n2. **BD GLSL Batch** — inline GLSL ES 3.0 shader applies a soft-light skin tint per iteration. `vary_floats` drives 4 skin tones (light → dark → zombie) in one workflow execution.\n3. **BD Save Batch** — `fc0_batch` + `iteration_names` → one PNG per tone, named by label.\n\n## Customizing skin tones\nEdit `vary_floats` in **BD GLSL Batch** to change the RGB values per iteration:\n- `u_float0=0.95,0.72,0.49,0.43`  — red channel (light→zombie)\n- `u_float1=0.82,0.62,0.41,0.56`  — green channel (zombie gets a green lift)\n- `u_float2=0.72,0.50,0.34,0.34`  — blue channel\n- `u_float3=0.4` in `floats`  — global tint strength\n\nEdit `iteration_names` to rename outputs (`light\\nmedium\\ndark\\nzombie`).\n\n## For production use\nPoint `fragment_shader_file` at your `skin_shader.glsl` (4-output ILM/SR/Unity/Unreal shader) and use `fc0..fc3` outputs. Use `save_only` / `pass_only` on BD Save Batch to filter which tones hit disk vs pass downstream.\n\n## VRAM\nRuns on GPU via GLSL — very fast. No AI model loaded.\n\n---\n**BrainDeadGuild** — created by **BizaNator**\n[BrainDeadGuild.com](https://BrainDeadGuild.com) · [BrainDead.TV](https://BrainDead.TV) · [GitHub](https://github.com/BizaNator/ComfyUI-BrainDead) · [Discord](https://braindeadguild.com/discord)\n"
      ]
    },
